      { name: "Azathioprine", type: "Immunosuppressant (Purine Analogue)", action: "Inhibits purine synthesis to reduce lymphocyte proliferation", sideEffects: "Bone marrow suppression, hepatotoxicity, GI upset", contra: "Pregnancy, TPMT deficiency", pearl: "Used as a steroid-sparing agent in relapsing COP. Check TPMT enzyme level before initiation to avoid severe myelosuppression." }
