      { name: "Ivermectin", type: "Antiparasitic", action: "Paralyzes and kills parasites by binding glutamate-gated chloride channels", sideEffects: "Dizziness, nausea, diarrhea, Mazzotti reaction in filariasis", contra: "Pregnancy, CNS disorders with impaired blood-brain barrier", pearl: "Consider empiric treatment for Strongyloides in at-risk patients before starting high-dose steroids. Steroid-induced immunosuppression can trigger fatal Strongyloides hyperinfection syndrome." }
